  <title>Template - Form builder</title>

  <section>
    <title>About Template</title>

    <para><indexterm class="singular">
        <primary>Form builder</primary>

        <secondary>Template</secondary>
      </indexterm>A template is an  <emphasis role="bold">electronic document form</emphasis>used for the eformsign service. It is an e-document transformed from existing paper forms such as applications, contracts, and agreements. You can create and upload templates in the eformsign service with its Web form designer or Form builder. For more information about the Web form designer, <xref linkend="template_wd"/>please refer to Chapter 5.</para>

    <section>
      <title>Overview of Template</title>

      <para>To create and send electronic documents via eformsign,  you have to create a template first which can be converted into an e-document.</para>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">How to create a template with Form builder</emphasis></para>

      <para>To create a template with Form builder, you must first download eformsign Form builder.</para>

      <note>
        <para>For more information about the Form builder,  <xref linkend="formbuilder"/>please refer to</para>
      </note>

      <para>MS Office files such as Word, Excel, and PowerPoint can be uploaded as a template using the eformsign Form builder.</para>

      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>Open a Word, Excel, or PowerPoint file.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Go to the OZ in Word (Excel or PPT) menu in the file.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Choose a location where to add a component.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Select a component type.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Adjust the size and position of the component.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Click the Action button to see the action of component.</emphasis> </para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Click the Upload button to upload the file as a template.</emphasis> </para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>

      <para><emphasis role="bold"/></para>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">Template settings</emphasis></para>

      <para>You can set the details for the template to be creates.</para>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">General</emphasis></para>

          <para>Set the template name, abbreviation, document name, document number, and etc.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Set permissions</emphasis></para>

          <para>Assign members or groups to grant permission to use the template to create documents and to manage documents created by the template.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Workflow</emphasis></para>

          <para>Sets the workflow for the document from its creation to completion.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Field</emphasis></para>

          <para>Sets default values, and auto-filled values for fields.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Notification settings </emphasis></para>

          <para>Sets channels, recipients, or notification messages of the notification to send when requesting or notifying status of documents created from the template.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Overview of Workflow</title>

      <para><indexterm class="singular">
          <primary>Workflow</primary>
        </indexterm>A workflow is a document process from its creation to completion.</para>

      <para>The workflow can be set in <emphasis role="bold">Template settings</emphasis>
      > <emphasis role="bold">Workflow</emphasis>for each template by a template manager.</para>

      <para>The default workflow consists of <emphasis role="bold">Start and Complete</emphasis>steps. You can add as many of the steps as you like including <emphasis role="bold"> Approver</emphasis>, <emphasis role="bold">Internal recipients</emphasis>, <emphasis role="bold">External recipients</emphasis> and create customized workflow for each template.</para>

      <figure>
        <title>Workflow steps</title>

        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata contentwidth="276"
                       fileref="resources/workflow-step-basic.PNG"/>
          </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Approval</emphasis></para>

          <para>Step to request an approval of e-document to a member in your company.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Internal recipients</emphasis></para>

          <para>Sending an e-document to a member in your company to review and sign.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">External recipients</emphasis></para>

          <para>Sending an e-document to a user outside of your company to review and sign.</para>

          <important>
            <para>What is difference between Approval and Internal recipient step?</para>

            <para>Both the approver and internal recipients can approve or reject the requested document, but internal recipients can designate next person to process the document.</para>

            <para>That is, internal recipients can designate external recipient, internal recipient, or approver after the Internal recipient’s step.</para>

            <para>For example, if you do not specify an approval line for another department, and you want to request to another department for that document, you can specify a contact for that other department as an internal recipient step. When processing documents, personnel from other department can set up separate approval lines for that department to process documents.</para>
          </important>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Template settings</title>

    <para>You can set the details for the template created with the uploaded file.</para>

    <note>
      <para>Only the company administrator or Template manager can perform this action.</para>

      <para>This work can be done in the PC, mobile, and application.</para>
    </note>

    <para><emphasis role="bold">How to go to the template setting screen </emphasis></para>

    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>In the sidebar menu, click and go to the  <emphasis role="bold">Manage templates</emphasis>menu.</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Click the name or settings icon() of the desired template.<inlinemediaobject>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata contentwidth="28" fileref="resources/config-icon.PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </inlinemediaobject></para>

        <para><inlinemediaobject>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata fileref="resources/template-settings.png" width="700"/>
            </imageobject>
          </inlinemediaobject></para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>

    <section>
      <title>General</title>

      <figure>
        <title>Template settings > General</title>

        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="resources/template-setting-general-formbuilder.png"
                       width="700"/>
          </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>

      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><emphasis role="bold">Configure basic settings for the template</emphasis></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Set basic information about the template including the template name, category, validity period, and etc.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>① Form file</term>

          <listitem>
            <para><emphasis role="bold">The name of the form file which is uploaded to eformsign from Word, Power point, or Excel using Form builder.</emphasis> To change the form file name, you need to change the file name of the uploaded Word, PowerPoint, or Excel file and then update it.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>② Template name</term>

          <listitem>
            <para><emphasis role="bold">The template name will be displayed on the Manage Templates</emphasis>and  <emphasis
            role="bold">New document</emphasis> menu pages.</para>

            <para><emphasis role="bold">Template Name</emphasis>should be 11 characters, including spaces. If the name is longer than 11 characters, you can see the full name by hovering the mouse over the name.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term/>

          <listitem>
            <figure>
              <title>Template Name</title>

              <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata fileref="resources/template-name.png" width="250"/>
                </imageobject>
              </mediaobject>
            </figure>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>③ Template abbreviation</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>A short name that briefly describing the template. It is recommended to use two or three words.</para>

            <para><emphasis role="bold">Template abbreviation</emphasis>can be used in the document number, document name, mail template, etc.by entering  <emphasis role="bold">$$</emphasis>.</para>

            <figure>
              <title>Template abbreviation</title>

              <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata fileref="resources/template-short-name.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </mediaobject>
            </figure>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>④ Category</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Category is used to sort templates by type. With the category name, <emphasis role="bold">templates in the Manage templates and documents in Document box and Manage documents can be filtered. </emphasis> <emphasis role="bold"></emphasis><emphasis role="bold"></emphasis>  You can choose from an existing category or create a new category by entering a new name.</para>

            <para>You can set multi-level categories with separator ( <emphasis role="bold">/ </emphasis>). For example, if you set the category <emphasis
            role="bold">HR Team/Vacation</emphasis>, the Vacation category in the HR category are created. <emphasis
            role="bold"></emphasis>  <emphasis
            role="bold"></emphasis> </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>⑤ Description</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Enter additional comments about the template. This description is displayed in the list and at the bottom of the template name in New document.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>⑥ Template validity period</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Sets the time period in which documents can be created from this template. The start date is set to the uploaded date as a default and you can change the date.</para>

            <para><emphasis role="bold">When No expiry date is checked</emphasis>, the document can be created with out time limit. <emphasis role="bold">If you uncheck No expiry date option and set the date, the document can only be created until the set date.</emphasis> </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>Document settings</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Configure additional settings including document naming rules for documents created from the template.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>⑦ Document naming rule</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Sets the document name when creating the document from the template. If a document naming rule is not set, the template name will be the document name.</para>

            <para>You can add reserved words in the document name using  <emphasis role="bold">$$</emphasis>and <emphasis
            role="bold">{{</emphasis>.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>⑧ Allow document name change</term>

          <listitem>
            <para><emphasis role="bold">If Allow document name change</emphasis>is checked, <emphasis
            role="bold">the document creator</emphasis> can change the document name.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>⑨ Generate a document number</term>

          <listitem>
            <para><indexterm class="singular">
                <primary>Template</primary>

                <secondary>Generate a document number</secondary>
              </indexterm>If Generate a document number is checked, documents are automatically numbered. Select the document number format that you want and when to be numbered.</para>

            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="resources/template-setting-general-doc-numering.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>⑩ Skip pop-up window when sending documents</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Use it when many documents are created and submitted. If this option is unchecked,<emphasis role="bold"> a pop-up window to enter message will appear.</emphasis>  <emphasis
            role="bold">When Skip pop-up window when sending documents</emphasis>is checked, <emphasis
            role="bold">the pop-up window does not appear and go to the next step.</emphasis> </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>General > Setting document naming rule</title>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">In Template settings,</emphasis>you can set the document naming rule for which created by the template.<indexterm class="singular">
          <primary>Template</primary>

          <secondary>Document naming rules</secondary>
        </indexterm></para>

      <para>You can make a piece of information entered into a document or document-related information to be automatically entered into the document name. If you set the document naming rule, then the document name is automatically entered based on the information of the document. As well, you can see this name in all document pages (In progress, Action required and All documents) and the Manage document page.</para>

      <note>
        <para>Only the <emphasis role="bold">company administrator </emphasis> or<emphasis
        role="bold"> Template manager</emphasis> can perform this action.</para>
      </note>

      <figure>
        <title>Manage documents > Documents list</title>

        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="resources/document-list.png" width="700"/>
          </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>

      <para/>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">How to set the document naming rule</emphasis></para>

      <figure>
        <title>Template settings > Setting the document naming rule</title>

        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="resources/template-setting-general-doc-numering_rule.png"
                       width="600"/>
          </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>

      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>In the sidebar menu, click and go to the <emphasis role="bold"> Manage templates</emphasis>menu.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Click on the <emphasis role="bold">settings</emphasis>icon (<inlinemediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata contentwidth="33"
                           fileref="resources/config-icon.PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </inlinemediaobject>) of the desired template <emphasis role="bold">to go to the Template settings</emphasis> page.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold"> </emphasis>Enter the desired naming rule in the  <emphasis
          role="bold">Document naming rule</emphasis> field in the General tab.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Click the<emphasis role="bold"> Save </emphasis>button on the top right corner to save the changes.</para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">How to use reserved words<indexterm class="singular">
          <primary>Template</primary>

          <secondary>Reserved word</secondary>
        </indexterm></emphasis></para>

      <figure>
        <title>Setting document naming rules using reserved words</title>

        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata contentwidth="500"
                       fileref="resources/template-setting-general-doc-numering_rule_reserved.png"/>
          </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>

      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><emphasis role="bold">{{</emphasis></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>This symbol adds a piece of information in the document into the document name.</para>

            <para><emphasis role="bold"> </emphasis>Enter <emphasis
            role="bold">{{</emphasis>in the Document naming rule field to display the list of Component IDs and then select the desired component ID. The information in that particular component will be added to the document name.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term><emphasis role="bold">$$</emphasis></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>This symbol adds document-related information into the document name.</para>

            <para><emphasis role="bold"></emphasis> Enter <emphasis
            role="bold">$$</emphasis>in the Document naming rule field to display the drop-down menu and then select the desired information.</para>

            <informaltable>
              <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec align="center" colwidth="323*"/>

                <colspec colwidth="677*"/>

                <thead>
                  <row>
                    <entry align="center">Information types</entry>

                    <entry align="center">Description</entry>
                  </row>
                </thead>

                <tbody>
                  <row>
                    <entry>Current_date</entry>

                    <entry>The date in which the document is created (e.g. Feb 20, 2020)</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Current_time</entry>

                    <entry>The time in which the document is created (e.g. 02:59 pm)</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Current_datetime</entry>

                    <entry>The date and time in which the document is created (e.g. Feb 20, 2020, 02:59 pm)</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Creator_ID</entry>

                    <entry>The ID of the member who created the document</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Creator_name</entry>

                    <entry>The name of the member who created the document</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Creator_dept</entry>

                    <entry>The department of the member who created the document</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Creator_company Name</entry>

                    <entry>The name of the company in which the member who created the document belongs to.</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Template_name</entry>

                    <entry>The template name entered in Template settings > General</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Template_abbreviation</entry>

                    <entry>The template abbreviation entered in Template settings > General</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Company</entry>

                    <entry>The company name entered in Manage company > Company profile</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Company_address</entry>

                    <entry>The address entered in Manage company > Company profile</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Company_contact_no</entry>

                    <entry>The contact information entered in Manage company > Company profile</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Company_registration_no</entry>

                    <entry>The business registration number entered in Manage company > Company profile</entry>
                  </row>

                  <row>
                    <entry>Company_homepage</entry>

                    <entry>Homepage URL entered in Manage company > Company profile</entry>
                  </row>
                </tbody>
              </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>

      <tip>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">Check the status of Allow document name change field.</emphasis> </para>

        <para>Even if the document naming rule is set, if the  <emphasis role="bold">Allow document name change </emphasis>option is checked, the document creator can arbitrarily change the document name. If you do not want the document name to be changed, then make sure to uncheck the
        <emphasis role="bold">Allow document name change</emphasis>option.</para>
      </tip>

