    <section>
      <title>Field</title>

      <para><emphasis role="bold"><indexterm class="singular">
          <primary>Template</primary>

          <secondary>Field</secondary>
        </indexterm>In the Field menu,</emphasis>you can set default values or autofill values for fields in the template, and adjust the order of the fields.</para>

      <figure>
        <title>Template settings > Field</title>

        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="resources/template-setting-FB-field-setting.png"
                       width="700"/>
          </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>

      <para>You can set the default value for the field to be entered company/group/member information saved in Manage custom fields, or set to choose from a recent input value, or set to type in by the user.</para>

      <para/>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">How to configure autofill</emphasis></para>

      <para>You can save information that are frequently entered into a document in advance and set to be auto-filled.</para>

      <para>For example, you can pre-save information about your company or group, such as department name, leader, representative number and information on document creator including name, contact details and etc. You can add items for related fields and set default values in <emphasis
      role="bold">Manage company > Manage custom fields</emphasis></para>

      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">In the Manage custom fields screen,</emphasis> add a field.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Go to Manage templates</emphasis> menu.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Click the Template settings icon.</emphasis> </para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Go to the Field</emphasis> menu.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Enter a default value for the field that you want to set to be auto-filled.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>After completing all the settings, click <emphasis role="bold">the Save</emphasis> button.</para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Notification settings</title>

      <para><indexterm class="singular">
          <primary>Template</primary>

          <secondary>Notification settings</secondary>
        </indexterm>You can select the method to send request or status notification message to recipients, view and edit the messages for documents created from the template.</para>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">Notification methods</emphasis></para>

      <para>Select the methods to send notifications to internal and external recipients. <emphasis
      role="bold">You can select</emphasis> either email <emphasis role="bold">or </emphasis>SMS or both.</para>

      <note>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">SMS</emphasis>can only be selected by a company subscribed a paid plan, and extra charges will apply.</para>
      </note>

      <para>When SMS is selected, <emphasis role="bold">Send via SMS and</emphasis>Send via SMS if failed to send via KakaoTalk are enabled. <emphasis
      role="bold"></emphasis></para>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Send SMS</emphasis>: Send a notification to recipients via SMS.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Send via KakaoTalk and if fails, send via SMS</emphasis>: Send a notification to recipients via KakaoTalk and to the recipient who does not use KakaoTalk, send via SMS.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

      <figure>
        <title>Notification methods</title>

        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="resources/template-setting-notification-channel.png"/>
          </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">Edit notification messages</emphasis></para>

      <para>You can view and edit notification messages that will be sent to recipients when requesting documents created from the template. Each notification template message is set as a default that is in <emphasis role="bold">Manage company > Notification template management</emphasis> page. Click the  <emphasis role="bold">Edit </emphasis>button to edit the message directly.</para>

      <para/>

      <note>
        <para>SMS templates can only be edited by companies subscribed a paid plan.</para>
      </note>

      <para>Each notification template message is set as a default that is in <emphasis role="bold">Manage company > Notification template management</emphasis> page. Click the  <emphasis
      role="bold">Edit</emphasis>button to edit the message directly.</para>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="resources/template-setting-notification-edit.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>

      <para/>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="resources/template-setting-notification-edit-email.png"
                     width="700"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>

      <para/>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When sending for review and sign > Internal</emphasis>: You can edit request notification messages sending to internal recipients when requesting for review and sign.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When sending for review and sign > External</emphasis>: You can edit request notification messages sending to external recipients when requesting for review and sign.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When sending for approval</emphasis>: You can edit the request notification message sending to approvers when requesting approval.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When rejecting documents</emphasis>: You can edit the request notification message sent to document requestors when a document is rejected by the approver, internal recipients, or external recipients.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

      <para><emphasis role="bold">Document status notifications</emphasis></para>

      <para>You can select recipients of status notifications for documents created from the template and allows you to preview (notification for approve/review and create/reject/void/correct) or edit (notification sent when documents are completed) messages.</para>

      <note>
        <para>For the notifications sent when documents are rejected, voided, and corrected, only email templates are provided and they are not sent via SMS.</para>

        <para>SMS templates for document completion notification (internal/external) can only be edited by companies subscribed a paid plan.</para>
      </note>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="resources/template-setting-notification-status.png"
                     width="500"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>

      <para/>

      <note>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">When Document creator </emphasis>option is checked and <emphasis
        role="bold">Step handler </emphasis>option is unchecked, a status notification is sent to the person who originally created the document.</para>

        <para><emphasis role="bold">When Document creator</emphasis> option is unchecked and <emphasis
        role="bold">Step handler </emphasis>option is checked, status notifications are sent to people who have processed the document before the current step, except the document creator.</para>

        <para><emphasis role="bold">When the options for Document creator </emphasis>and  <emphasis
        role="bold">Step handler</emphasis>  are both checked, status notifications are sent to both the document creator and the people who have processed the document before the current step. </para>

        <para><emphasis role="bold">When Document creator</emphasis>and  <emphasis
        role="bold">Step handler</emphasis> options are both unchecked, no status notification of that step will be sent.</para>
      </note>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When documents are approved</emphasis>: When the document is approved by approver, a notification will be sent that the document has been approved.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When documents are reviewed and signed</emphasis>: When the documents are reviewed and signed by internal or external recipients, the notification will be sent that the document has been reviewed and signed.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When documents are rejected</emphasis>: When the document is rejected by approver, internal or external recipients, a notification will be sent that the document has been rejected.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">Document void notification</emphasis>: When the request for voiding document is approved, a notification will be sent that the document has been voided.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When documents are corrected</emphasis>: When the document is corrected by document creator, a notification will be sent that the document has been corrected.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When documents are completed > Internal</emphasis>: When the document is completed, a notification will be sent to the document creator, approvers, and internal recipients that the document has been completed.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><emphasis role="bold">When documents are completed > External</emphasis>: When the document is completed, a notification will be sent to external recipients that the document has been completed.</para>

          <note>
            <para><emphasis role="bold">When the Document creator option for When the document is completed > External</emphasis>is checked and external recipients create and submit a document via a URL, an information to receive a notification when the document is completed should be entered and the notification will be sent to the external recipients.<emphasis role="bold"></emphasis> </para>
          </note>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </section>
  </section>

